---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Example Reconstruction | Prima Veritas">

<main class="flex-1">

  <!-- HERO -->
  <section class="border-b border-white/10">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
      <h1 class="font-sans text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight text-off-white leading-tight">
        Example Reconstruction
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-xl text-off-white/80">
        A concrete example of how a fragmented operational event history becomes a sealed, reproducible chain.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>


<!-- SCENARIO -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Scenario
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">
      <p>
        A set of operational logs tracks updates to an order across multiple systems:
        order management, customer support, and fulfillment.
      </p>

      <p>
        Each system records events independently. Timestamps drift. Field formats differ.
        Identifiers are inconsistent. No single system preserves the full history.
      </p>

      <p>
        The result is a fragmented view of what actually happened.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- RAW INTAKE -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">

    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Raw intake
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-10 max-w-5xl text-sm text-off-white/80">

      <div>
        <strong>Order System</strong><br/>
        <code class="block mt-2 text-off-white/60">
          14:02:11 ORDER_7421 → CREATED<br/>
          14:05:33 ADDRESS UPDATED
        </code>
      </div>

      <div>
        <strong>Support Log</strong><br/>
        <code class="block mt-2 text-off-white/60">
          Ticket opened for order 7421<br/>
          Customer requested delivery change
        </code>
      </div>

      <div>
        <strong>Fulfillment Record</strong><br/>
        <code class="block mt-2 text-off-white/60">
          Shipment scheduled<br/>
          Delivery attempt recorded
        </code>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-10 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80">
      <strong>Observed Issues</strong>
      <ul class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-off-white/60">
        <li>Timestamp drift</li>
        <li>Non-uniform identifiers (ORDER_7421 vs 7421 vs free text)</li>
        <li>Missing cross-reference keys</li>
        <li>Events spread across unrelated systems</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>


<!-- CANONICAL EVENT ENVELOPE -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Canonical envelope normalization
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">
      <p>
        Each raw record is transformed into a canonical envelope: unified timestamp,
        source identifier, schema version, and structured payload.
      </p>

      <code class="block mt-4 text-off-white/60">
{`{
  event_id: "e1032",
  source: "order.system",
  timestamp: "2026-04-12T14:02:11Z",
  payload: {
    order_id: "7421",
    status: "CREATED"
  }
}`}
      </code>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- EVENT CHAIN -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Event chain construction
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">
      <p>
        Each envelope is hashed. The hash of the prior event is embedded in the next.
        Order is explicit. Mutation invalidates the sequence.
      </p>

      <code class="block mt-4 text-off-white/60">
{`e1032 → hash: a94f...
e1033 → prev_hash: a94f...
e1034 → prev_hash: b221...`}
      </code>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- RECONSTRUCTION -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Deterministic reconstruction
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">
      <p>
        From the ordered chain, system state at any point in time can be reconstructed.
      </p>

      <p>
        Order creation, address changes, support intervention, and delivery attempts
        are derived from a single unified history.
      </p>

      <p>
        Given the same input chain, reconstruction output is identical across environments.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>


<!-- VERIFICATION -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-10">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Independent verification
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-6 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80 space-y-4">
      <p>
        The final bundle contains the full event sequence and hash lineage.
      </p>

      <p>
        A third party can validate structural integrity and ordering without access
        to the original systems.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- RUN YOUR OWN RECONSTRUCTION -->
<section class="border-b border-white/10">
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">

    <h2 class="text-lg font-sans tracking-tight text-off-white">
      Generate Verification Artifact
    </h2>

    <p class="mt-4 max-w-4xl text-sm text-off-white/80">
      Upload a CSV to generate a deterministic verification artifact.
    </p>

    <!-- UPLOAD -->
    <div class="mt-10 flex flex-col md:flex-row md:items-center gap-6">

      <label class="bg-charcoal border border-white/10 text-off-white text-sm px-4 py-2 cursor-pointer hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">
        Select CSV File
        <input type="file" accept=".csv" class="hidden" />
      </label>

      <button id="generate-btn"
        class="bg-carbon-navy font-semibold text-sm border border-white/20 px-4 py-2 min-w-[180px] flex items-center justify-center gap-2">
        
        <span id="btn-text">Generate Artifact</span>
        <span id="btn-spinner" class="hidden w-4 h-4 border-2 border-white/40 border-t-white rounded-full animate-spin"></span>

      </button>

      <a href="/sample.csv" download
        class="nav-link text-sm opacity-75 hover:text-[var(--accent)]">
        Download Sample CSV →
      </a>

    </div>
    
      <div id="status-message" class="text-sm min-h-[1.25rem] opacity-0"></div>

          <!-- SUCCESS STATE -->
    <div class="max-w-4xl">
      <div id="result"
        class="mt-6 border border-white/10 p-6 text-sm text-off-white/80 hidden">
      <p class="text-off-white font-semibold mb-4">Artifact Generated Successfully</p>

      <div class="mt-6 text-off-white/60 space-y-4">
        <div>
          <div>Artifact Hash</div>
          <div id="artifact-hash" class="font-mono break-all">—</div>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div>Event Count</div>
          <div id="event-count" class="font-mono">—</div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6">
        <a href="https://api.primaveritas.io/download/bundle.zip"
          class="bg-carbon-navy font-semibold text-sm border border-white/20 px-4 py-2 inline-block hover:text-[var(--accent)] transition-colors">
          Download Artifact
        </a>
      </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  
      <!-- Error Section -->
      <div id="error-section" class="mt-6 border border-red-400/30 p-6 text-sm hidden max-w-4xl">
        <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold mb-4">Upload Failed</p>
        <ul id="error-list" class="space-y-4 text-off-white/70"></ul>
      </div>

      <details class="mt-6 text-off-white/70">
        <summary class="cursor-pointer">View File Requirements</summary>

      <div class="mt-4 space-y-4 text-off-white/60">

        <p><strong>Required Fields</strong><br/>
        Your CSV must include the following columns:<br/>
        timestamp, stream_id, event_type, actor, object, notes</p>

        <p>Column order does not matter.<br/>
        Additional columns are not currently supported.<br/>
        All required fields must be present.</p>

        <p>Timestamps must be ISO 8601 with timezone.<br/>
        Example: 2024-01-01T10:00:00Z</p>

      </div>

      </details>

      <div class="mt-6 space-y-4 text-off-white/80">

        <p>
          Prima Veritas does not modify or infer missing data. Inputs must match the required format
          to ensure deterministic, reproducible results.
        </p>

        <p>
          Do not upload sensitive or personal data. Files are processed for demonstration purposes only.
        </p>

      </div>

</section>

        <script>
          const fileInput = document.querySelector('input[type="file"]');
          const button = document.getElementById("generate-btn");
          const statusEl = document.getElementById("status-message");

          let fileSelected = false;
          let artifactGenerated = false;

          fileInput.addEventListener("change", () => {
            fileSelected = true;
            artifactGenerated = false;

            const file = fileInput.files[0];

            statusEl.textContent = file ? file.name : "";
            statusEl.classList.remove("opacity-0", "text-red-400");
            statusEl.classList.add("text-off-white/60");

            // Reset button state
            button.disabled = false;
            document.getElementById("btn-text").textContent = "Generate Artifact";
            document.getElementById("btn-spinner").classList.add("hidden");

            // Reset error section
            document.getElementById("error-section").classList.add("hidden");
            document.getElementById("error-list").innerHTML = "";
          });

          button.addEventListener("click", async () => {

            const file = fileInput.files[0];

            if (!fileSelected || !file || artifactGenerated) {
              statusEl.textContent = "No file selected.";
              statusEl.classList.remove("opacity-0", "text-off-white/60");
              statusEl.classList.add("text-red-400");
              return;
            }

            button.disabled = true;
            document.getElementById("btn-spinner").classList.remove("hidden");

            try {
              const formData = new FormData();
              formData.append("file", file);

              const res = await fetch("https://api.primaveritas.io/artifact", {
                method: "POST",
                body: formData
              });

              const raw = await res.json();

              //  NEW: handle backend error shape
              if (!res.ok || raw.status === "error") {
                if (Array.isArray(raw.errors)) {
                  const errorSection = document.getElementById("error-section");
                  const errorList = document.getElementById("error-list");

                  errorList.innerHTML = raw.errors.map(e => {
                    let message = "";
                    let fix = "";

                    if (e.field === "timestamp" && e.reason === "missing_value") {
                      message = "Row " + e.row + " is missing a timestamp.";
                      fix = "Add one like 2024-01-01T10:00:00Z.";
                    } else if (e.field === "timestamp" && e.reason === "invalid_value") {
                      message = "Row " + e.row + " has an invalid timestamp.";
                      fix = "Use ISO format like 2024-01-01T10:00:00Z.";
                    } else if (e.reason === "missing_columns" || e.field === "header") {
                      message = "Your CSV is missing required columns.";
                      fix = "Make sure it includes: timestamp, stream_id, event_type, actor, object, notes.";
                    } else if (e.reason === "column_count_mismatch") {
                      message = "Row " + e.row + " does not match the expected structure.";
                      fix = "Each row must contain exactly 6 columns.";
                    } else {
                      message = e.hint || "An unexpected error occurred.";
                      fix = "";
                    }

                    let fixHtml = "";
                    if (fix) {
                      fixHtml = '<div class="text-off-white/50">' + fix + '</div>';
                    }

                    return '<li class="space-y-1"><div class="text-off-white/80">' + message + '</div>' + fixHtml + '</li>';
                  }).join("");

                  errorSection.classList.remove("hidden");
                } else {
                  statusEl.textContent = "Unknown error";
                  statusEl.classList.remove("opacity-0", "text-off-white/60");
                  statusEl.classList.add("text-red-400");
                }
                return;
              }

              const hashEl = document.getElementById("artifact-hash");

              if (typeof raw.artifact_hash === "string" && raw.artifact_hash.length > 0) {
                hashEl.textContent = raw.artifact_hash;
              } else {
                hashEl.textContent = "Hash unavailable";
                hashEl.classList.add("text-off-white/50");
              }

              document.getElementById("event-count").textContent = raw.event_count;
              document.getElementById("result").classList.remove("hidden");

              artifactGenerated = true;

            } catch (err) {
              statusEl.textContent = "Network or server error";
              statusEl.classList.remove("opacity-0", "text-off-white/60");
              statusEl.classList.add("text-red-400");
            } finally {
              await new Promise(r => setTimeout(r, 400));
              button.disabled = false;
              document.getElementById("btn-text").textContent = "Generate Artifact";
              document.getElementById("btn-spinner").classList.add("hidden");
            }

          });
        </script>

</main>

</Layout>